objkey.comment: objkey - STRING  - Header keyword recording the object type.

obskey.comment: obskey - STRING  - Header keyword recording the observation type.

obskeyb.comment: obskeyb - STRING - Value of the observation type header keyword for a bias frame.

obskeyd.comment: obskeyd - STRING - Value of the observation type header keyword for a dark frame.

obskeyf.comment: obskeyf - STRING - Value of the observation type header keyword for a flat frame.

obskeys.comment: obskeys - STRING - Value of the observation type header keyword for a science frame.

datekey.comment: datekey - STRING - Header keyword recording the date (universal time) at the start of the observation. The value of this keyword should be a STRING of the format YYYY-MM-DDxxx...xxx where YYYY-MM-DD is a valid date and xxx...xxx represents a string of arbitrary characters of any length.

timekey.comment: timekey - STRING - Header keyword recording the universal time at the start of the observation. The value of this keyword should be a NUMBER in hours, or a STRING of the format HH:MM:SS.SSS, where HH:MM:SS.SSS is a valid time.

rakey.comment: rakey - STRING - Header keyword recording the right ascension (J2000) of the observation. The value of this keyword should be a STRING of the format HH:MM:SS.SSS, where HH:MM:SS.SSS is a valid time.

deckey.comment: deckey - STRING - Header keyword recording the declination (J2000) of the observation. The value of this keyword should be a STRING of the format pDD:MM:SS.SSS, where pDD:MM:SS.SSS is an angle between +-90 degrees in sexagesimal format.

expkey.comment: expkey - STRING - Header keyword recording the image exposure time in seconds. The value of this keyword should be a NUMBER with a non-negative value, or a STRING that represents a valid non-negative number.

filtkey.comment: filtkey - STRING - Header keyword recording the filter employed. The value of this keyword should be a STRING.

pix_scale.comment: pix_scale - DOUBLE - The pixel scale in arcsec per pixel

fov.comment: fov - DOUBLE - Field of view of the CCD camera (deg). This parameter should be positive and less than or equal to 90.0 (Default value = 0.1).

gain.comment: gain - DOUBLE - CCD gain (e-/ADU). This parameter should be positive (Default value = 1.0)

ron.comment: ron - DOUBLE - CCD readout noise (ADU). This parameter should be non-negative (Default value = 0.0)

imagex1.comment: imagex1 - INT - Image region bottom left hand corner (x1,y1) and top right hand corner (x2,y2) in pixel number coordinates.

imagex2.comment: imagex2 - INT - Image region bottom left hand corner (x1,y1) and top right hand corner (x2,y2) in pixel number coordinates.

imagey1.comment: imagey1 - INT - Image region bottom left hand corner (x1,y1) and top right hand corner (x2,y2) in pixel number coordinates.

imagey2.comment: imagey2 - INT - Image region bottom left hand corner (x1,y1) and top right hand corner (x2,y2) in pixel number coordinates.

maxval.comment: maxval - DOUBLE - Maximum useful pixel value in a raw image (ADU).

minval.comment: minval - DOUBLE - Minimum useful pixel value in a raw image (ADU).

moondkey.comment: moondkey - STRING - Header keyword recording the Lunar distance from target (deg).

moonfkey.comment: moonfkey - STRING - Header keyword recording the Lunar distance from target (deg).

oscanx1.comment: oscanx1 - INT - Overscan region bottom left hand corner (x1,y1) and top right hand corner (x2,y2) in pixel number coordinates.

oscanx2.comment: oscanx2 - INT - Overscan region bottom left hand corner (x1,y1) and top right hand corner (x2,y2) in pixel number coordinates.

oscany1.comment: oscany1 - INT - Overscan region bottom left hand corner (x1,y1) and top right hand corner (x2,y2) in pixel number coordinates.

oscany2.comment: oscany2 - INT - Overscan region bottom left hand corner (x1,y1) and top right hand corner (x2,y2) in pixel number coordinates.
